.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blockchain Utilities</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ethgasstation.info/\">ETH Gas Station</a> - A tool to check the current price of gas for transactions.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Protocols</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Whisper-pages\">Whisper</a> - A communication protocol for DApps to communicate with each other.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Protocols</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/web3.js\">Web3.js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/web3.js\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":10271,\"repo\":\"ethereum/web3.js\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Ethereum's JavaScript API.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereumbook/ethereumbook\">Mastering Ethereum</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ethereumbook/ethereumbook\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">8.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":8484,\"repo\":\"ethereumbook/ethereumbook\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A developers guide to the operation and use of Ethereum.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://the-eye.eu/public/Books/qt.vidyagam.es/library/humble-bitcoin-bundle/Introducing%20Ethereum%20and%20Solidity_%20Foud%20Blockchain%20Programming%20for%20Beginners/Introducing%20Ethereum%20and%20Solidity_%20Foundatiin%20Programming%20for%20Beginners%20-%20Chris%20Dannen.pdf\">Introduction to Ethereum and Solidity</a> - Learn Solidity development from concept to deployment.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32762240-ethereum\">Ethereum: Blockchains, Digital Assets, Smart Contracts, Decentralized Autonomous Organizations</a> - Learn about Ethereum (and blockchains) from an IBM blockchain liason.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Misc</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ethgasstation.info/\">ETH Gas Station</a> - A tool to check the current price of gas for transactions.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Official</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/\">Ethereum GitHub</a></li>","updatedAt":"2019-01-23T18:59:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Protocols</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Sharding-introduction-R&#x26;D-compendium\">Sharding</a> - Partitioning computational resources so that nodes do not have to process the entire blockchain.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-28T15:46:27.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Protocols</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>zk-SNARKS - Verify knowledge of a secret without revealing it.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://media.consensys.net/introduction-to-zksnarks-with-examples-3283b554fc3b\">Introduction to zk-SNARKS with examples</a> - A practical overview of zk-SNARKS.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jstoxrocky/zksnarks_example\">A practical beginner's guide to creating, proving, and verifying zkSNARKs</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jstoxrocky/zksnarks_example\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">226</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":226,\"repo\":\"jstoxrocky/zksnarks_example\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Introduction to zk-SNARKS and implementation as a smart contract.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@VitalikButerin/zk-snarks-under-the-hood-b33151a013f6\">zk-SNARKS: Under the Hood</a> - Technical explanation of zk-SNARKS.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.ethereum.org/2016/12/05/zksnarks-in-a-nutshell/\">zk-SNARKs in a nutshell</a> - Technical explanation of zk-SNARKS.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://coders-errand.com/practical-zk-snarks-for-ethereum/\">Practical zk-SNARKs for Ethereum</a> - A short and practical introduction to using zk-SNARKs.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-18T20:34:26.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.codementor.io/learn/blockchain/solidity-tutorials\">Various Ethereum &#x26; Solidity Tutorials</a> - How to create smart contracts, deploy your own DApps, create tokens, and more — from beginner to intermediate topics.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-16T11:58:59.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cryptozombies.io/\">CryptoZombies</a> - Learn to Code Ethereum DApps By Building Your Own Game.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/ethereum/comments/9h0w83/start_ethereum_dapp_development_career_ultimate/\">Start Ethereum DApp Development Career</a> - Informal guide to starting developing DApps.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ethereum.meta.stackexchange.com/questions/431/faq-frequently-asked-questions-and-reference-answers\">Ethereum Stack Exchange</a> - Question and answers about Ethereum.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Safety\">Smart contract safety</a> - Ethereum wiki on best practices for safety in smart contracts.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hudsonjameson.com/2017-06-27-accounts-transactions-gas-ethereum/\">Accounts, Transactions, Gas, and Block Gas Limits in Ethereum</a> - Functional description of Ethereum accounts, gas and transactions.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ethernaut.zeppelin.solutions/\">Ethernaut Smart Contract Capture the Flag</a> - Practice hacking Smart Contracts.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://novicedock.com/learn/cryptocurrency/ethereum\">Ethereum Syllabus</a> - Syllabus to learn Ethereum.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://soc1024.ece.illinois.edu/teaching/ece598am/fall2016/\">Cryptocurrency Security: University of Illinois 2016</a> - Cryptocurrency Security Course.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://crypto.stanford.edu/cs251_fall15/\">Stanford CS 251(p): Bitcoin and Crypto Currencies</a> - Stanford Bitcoin and Cryptocurrency Course.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://digitalcurrency.unic.ac.cy/free-introductory-mooc/\">Introduction to Digital Currencies: University of Nicosia</a> - Digital currency introductory MOOC.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://users.encs.concordia.ca/~clark/courses/1703-6630/index.html\">Bitcoin and Blockchain Technology: Concordia University</a> - Introduction to Bitcoin and blockchain technology MOOC.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://consensys.github.io/smart-contract-best-practices/\">Smart Contract Best Practices</a> - Security related best practices for smart contracts.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Philosophy</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2016/633.pdf\">Making Smart Contracts Smarter</a> - Smart contract security attacks.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-_Qs0XdPpw8\">Ethereum Explained (22:00)</a> - Introductory explanation to the Ethereum platform.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gSQXq2_j-mw\">A Guide to Building Your First Decentralized Application (37:00)</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blockchain Utilities</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ethplorer.io/\">Ethplorer</a> - Ethereum block explorer.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Blockchain Utilities</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.etherchain.org/\">Etherchain</a> - Ethereum block explorer.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Protocols</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Casper-Proof-of-Stake-compendium\">Casper</a> - Proof of Stake Implementation.\n<ul>\n<li>Casper CBC - Correct by Construction for full Proof-of-Stake.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/cbc-casper\">Code Repository</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/cbc-casper\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">216</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":216,\"repo\":\"ethereum/cbc-casper\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A python implementation of a class of correct-by-construction consensus protocols.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/cbc-casper/wiki\">CBC Wiki</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/research/blob/master/papers/cbc-consensus/AbstractCBC.pdf\">CBC Research Paper</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Casper FFG - Friendly Finality Gadget for PoS validation with Proof-of-Work.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/casper\">Code Repository</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/casper\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">666</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":666,\"repo\":\"ethereum/casper\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - The FFG contract, related software and tests.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1710.09437\">Casper the Friendly Finality Gadget Paper</a> - Research paper detailing FFG.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Proof-of-Stake-FAQs\">PoS FAQs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/31797/casper-ffg-vs-casper-ghost-cbc/31814#31814\">FFG vs CBC Comparison</a> - A Stack Exchange comparison of FFG and CBC.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Protocols</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Ethash\">Ethash Proof of Work</a> - Ethereum's Proof of Work Algorithm.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Misc</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/ethereum/\">r/Ethereum</a> - Ethereum subreddit.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Misc</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.meetup.com/find/?allMeetups=false&#x26;keywords=ethereum\">Ethereum Worldwide Meetups</a> - Meet up with the local Ethereum community via meetup.com.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:58:02.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Philosophy</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ethereum/ethereum.org/wiki/Philosophy\">Ethereum Wiki Philosophy</a> - Some of the core philosophies of Ethereum.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:22:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Philosophy</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eips.ethereum.org/\">Ethereum Improvement Proposals</a> - Standards for the Ethereum platform, including core protocol specifications, client APIs, and contract standards.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-11-01T10:22:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning and MOOCs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.bu.edu/~goldbe/projects/eclipseEth.pdf\">Low-Resource Eclipse Attacks on Ethereum’s Peer-to-Peer Network</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-24T22:01:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@merunasgrincalaitis/the-ultimate-end-to-end-tutorial-to-create-and-deploy-a-fully-descentralized-dapp-in-ethereum-18f0cf6d7e0e\">End to End DApp Tutorial</a> - Create a gambling DApp using Metamask, Truffle, Remix, React and IPFS.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-19T14:49:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://karl.tech/learning-solidity-part-1-deploy-a-contract/\">Learning Solidity Tutorial Series</a> - Building smart contracts with Metamask and Remix IDE.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-19T14:20:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blog.zeppelin.solutions/the-hitchhikers-guide-to-smart-contracts-in-ethereum-848f08001f05\">Hitchhikers Guide to Smart Contracts</a> - Build smart contracts on Ethereum using Truffle, testrpc and Solidity.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-08T19:47:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@ConsenSys/a-101-noob-intro-to-programming-smart-contracts-on-ethereum-695d15c1dab4\">A 101 Noob Intro to Programming Smart Contracts on Ethereum</a> - Smart contract tutorial with a focus on building up understanding before code.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-08T19:47:29.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wiki.parity.io/Dapp-Tutorial\">Parity DApp Tutorial</a> - 10 part tutorial on how to write DApps.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-08T19:47:29.000Z"},